ar.jpg class=headings><font color=#FFFFFF>Comment</font></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#484848><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub97.ezboard.com/uprojectorion.showPublicProfile?language=EN>projectorion</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Nuclear Renaissance Man</span><br>  Posts: 1526<br> <font color=#6F6F6F>(6/18/02 2:59 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub97.ezboard.com/fnuclearspacefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=534.topic>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.gothicbarbie.net/images/electric.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.nuclearspace.com/ezboard/images/posticons/7.gif" align=absmiddle>  Why are rockets so expensive?</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.xprize.org/images/photos_print/earth_med.jpg"><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--><br>
The Earth viewed from 100km up.<br>
<br>
Aren't they basically a tank? Nozzle at one end, fuel at the other. Add a few life supporting structures and cooling systems yadda yadda yadda. Couldn't anyone with garage tools throw one together? <br>
<br>
Why can't model rockets simply be scaled up? Why the insanely high cost? <p>
