<br>
GWt stands for gigawatts THERMAL.<br>
GWe stands for gigawatts ELECTRIC.<br>
<br>
Those are basic units used universal standards.<br>
<br>
From ANSTO, the  Australian Nuclear Science and Technology Organisation<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr>  GLOSSARY OF ABBREVIATIONS, ACRONYMS AND DEFINITIONS<br>
....<br>
GW Gigawatt<br>
 <br>
GWe / GWt Gigawatts of electrical / thermal power <br>
<br>
...<br>
<br>
MW Megawatt<br>
<br>
MWe / MWt Megawatts of electrical / thermal power <br>
<br>
...<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
A 2 GWt power plant produces roughly 650 MWe.<br>
<br>
The discrepancies are yours, not mine.<br>
