ke the Sea Dragon.  The Sea Dragon is one of the greastest trageties in the space program. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#484848><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub97.ezboard.com/uyales.showPublicProfile?language=EN>yales</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>MegaLipidCephaloid</span><br>  Posts: 448<br> <font color=#6F6F6F>(8/16/02 8:25 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub97.ezboard.com/fnuclearspacefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=534.topic&index=20>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://home.attbi.com/~yales/images/53invad2.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.nuclearspace.com/ezboard/images/posticons/radman.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: &quot;A Rocket a Day&quot;</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr>   We don't have any machine that can self-replicate itself. Actually, we do. They're called humans.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
